        "cooked": "<p>when rearranging folders, long hold on a folder opens a context menu.</p>\n<p>If you long hold the drag handle it also opens that context menu, but in my experience that is poor design. It’s quite normal to long hold a drag button while thinking about the direction you want to move, and when this context menu opens it block you from moving the item.</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/1/a/1ac6a879ce2ebaaed97ae3320e967e82d12290cc.png\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/1ac6a879ce2ebaaed97ae3320e967e82d12290cc\" title=\"Screenshot_20260101-230800.Signal\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/1/a/1ac6a879ce2ebaaed97ae3320e967e82d12290cc_2_224x500.png\" alt=\"Screenshot_20260101-230800.Signal\" data-base62-sha1=\"3OS2jfCUUWDGGnwDypDmsohpmlm\" width=\"224\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/1/a/1ac6a879ce2ebaaed97ae3320e967e82d12290cc_2_224x500.png, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/1/a/1ac6a879ce2ebaaed97ae3320e967e82d12290cc_2_336x750.png 1.5x, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/1/a/1ac6a879ce2ebaaed97ae3320e967e82d12290cc_2_448x1000.png 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"222124\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">Screenshot_20260101-230800.Signal</span><span class=\"informations\">1220×2712 178 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>I propose:</p>\n<p>option A - move the edit and the delere button directly to each list item (not hidden in a context menu). There is no visual cue that a context menu exists, like a 3 dot button. It could be missed, so it should just not be there.</p>\n<p>option B - exampt the drag handle from the long press action. Also add a 3 dot button on each item to hint at the existance of more options / a context menu. a short press on that button should suffice to open the context menu.</p>",
